job_details.Functieomschrijving:
The Linux team is continuously improving the current infrastructure landscape by automation and the use of new technologies. Besides ensuring excellent operations your activities will support the team in building and expanding (new) systems and platforms, enhancing existing infrastructure, the infra delivery to our internal customers, and carrying out life cycle management of systems and software.

   What we expect from you:
     * You are able to work in an autonomous and structured way;
     * You take initiative and collaborate well within team and with other colleagues;
     * You carry projects from the start to a maintainable solution including knowledge sharing;
     * Your communication and coordination skills are developed well;
     * You are enthusiastic, energetic and take ownership;
     * Action and results oriented;
     * You are creative and investigative;
     * You love to challenge people in a positive way;

   You will be part of the Cloud & Infrastructure Solutions team within our Network department. This team of around 30 people. Together with your direct colleagues you will be responsible for managing several external suppliers responsible for infrastructure on the supply side and work with Delivery & contract managers, Product Leads and Project managers and the demand side., At Odido we learn every day. All of us. You are responsible for your own development. That is why you decide how, what and when you learn. We have more than 200 digital training courses with which you can work on professional and personal goals. We don't do old-fashioned performance reviews and assessments. You keep your manager and colleagues informed of your goals and progress. You are in control.

